        " dialect - something that would heavily influence his work. Tremblays first professionally produced play,  Les Belles-Sœurs , was written in 1965 and premiered at the Théâtre du Rideau Vert on August 28, 1968. It transformed the old guard of Canadian theatre and introduced ": null
