        " to the mainstream. It stirred up controversy by portraying the lives of working class women and attacking the strait-laced, deeply religious society of mid-20th century Quebec.       The most profound and lasting effects of Tremblays early plays, including Hosanna and La Duchesse de Langeais, were the barriers they toppled in Quebec society.  Until the ": null
