        " The Arts Tonight, he remarked that he has always avoided behaviours he has considered masculine; for example, he does not smoke and he noted that he was 45 years old and did not know how to drive a car. I think I am a rare breed, he said, A homosexual who doesnt like men. He claims one of his biggest regrets in life was not telling his mother that he was gay, before she died.     His latest play to receive wide acclaim is  For the Pleasure of Seeing Her Again , a funny and nostalgic play, centered on the memories of his mother. He later published the Plateau Mont-Royal Chronicles, a cycle of six novels including  The Fat Woman Next Door is Pregnant   and  The Duchess and the Commoner  . The second novel of this series,  Therese and Pierrette and the Little Hanging Angel  , was one of the novels chosen for inclusion in the French version of  Canada Reads , Le combat des livres, broadcast on ": null
