        ", calling it stupid and stating that he thought it ridiculous to expect a housewife in Vancouver to be fluent in both English and French.   CBC  March 28, 1978     Despite his often outspoken views in public, Tremblays treatment of politics in his plays is subtle. Speaking of politics and the theatre in an ": null
